<SLUG> BC-HKN-COYOTES-EXPANSION-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COYOTES' UNPROTECTED LIST FEATURES SEVERAL SURPRISES 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By BOB MCMANAMAN  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX - The Coyotes protected several stars but exposed a few
surprise players to Friday's NHL expansion draft in Boston,
including forwards Bob Corkum and Jim Cummins and defensemen Stan
Neckar and Gerald Diduck, who is recovering from major knee
surgery.
</P>
<P>
   Other notable Phoenix players who will be made available to the
Atlanta Thrashers in this week's draft include goalies Mikhail
Shtalenkov and Jimmy Waite, defensemen J.J. Daigneault, Jamie
Huscroft, Sean Gagnon and Brad Tiley, and forwards Mike Sullivan,
Mike Stapleton, Brian Noonan, Stephen Leach and perhaps, Louie
DeBrusk or Tavis Hansen, ``The Arizona Republic'' has learned.
</P>
<P>
   Atlanta, which will select one player from each of the existing
27 clubs except for the second-year Nashville Predators, will draft
at least four goalies Friday despite acquiring Damian Rhodes in a
trade with Ottawa last week. A league-wide trading freeze was put
into effect on Sunday and will continue until the conclusion of
Friday's draft.
</P>
<P>
   The Coyotes had to submit their protected list to the NHL by
Monday afternoon. The list will be made official today.
</P>
<P>
   Cummins, an NHL-tested enforcer, and Shtalenkov, an experienced
backup goalie, figure to be two of the most likely candidates to be
nabbed by Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   Corkum, 31, the Coyotes' best defensive forward and top faceoff
man, might also be an intriguing pick, but he becomes an
unrestricted free agent on July 1 and may be difficult to sign.
</P>
<P>
   Another possibility is Neckar, 23, whom the Coyotes obtained
from the New York Rangers in March in exchange for defenseman Jason
Doig and a sixth-round pick in Saturday's NHL draft. He was a
regular player on the team's six-man defensive rotation.
</P>
<P>
   Younger Coyotes players, such as centers Daniel Briere and
Trevor Letowski, are exempt from the expansion draft. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
