   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ MIAMI _ One of society's great problems is
selective enforcement. Rules that were meant for everyone often are
applied only to certain people. That includes drinking beer in
public, especially if the beer is Old Milwaukee. (Howard Kleinberg
is a columnist for Cox News Service.) MOVED MONDAY.
