time I was 3 years old I visited my grandparents in a small town in
Alabama, and that place was more familiar to me than any of the
many towns where my parents and I lived during those years.
(Sinclair, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ A 25-year-old computer
programmer from Detroit has been found guilty of swearing with
vigor and frequency in front of children and faces a possible 90
days in jail. The American Civil Liberties Union is fighting the
conviction saying it clearly violates the Constitution. The
executive director of the Michigan ACLU reminds us that we hear
unpleasant language every day _ ``on the streets, on the radio and
television, in sports stadiums, and many other places.'' Yeah sure,
but that doesn't make it any less revolting. (Schuett, Cox News
Service) MOVED.
</P>
