<P>
   TOP-JUDGE _ COLUMBIA, S.C._When Jean Toal graduated from the
University of South Carolina Law School in 1968, several law firms
told her they would hire her as a secretary but not as a lawyer.
Now, at 55, her law rules. The Agnes Scott alumna and board member
has been elected South Carolina's first woman chief justice of the
supreme court. She has been called profane and insensitive,
irrespressible and brilliant. But her greatest pride, she says, is
being a successful wife and mother. She says of her husband, a law
school classmate, ``We are best friends, sweethearts, parents,
sports nuts, and we've raised two wonderful girls.'' (Riddle,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution; FREELANCER _ not for use by NYTNS
clients).
