Argentina's answer to Jay Leno, who tells jokes, interviews guests
_ and sips Budweiser from a can in front of 3.2 million viewers.
Thanks largely to Tinelli's endorsement, Budweiser's sales in
Argentina soared 61 percent in the first quarter of this year. And
Argentina is one of many overseas markets where Anheuser is pouring
it on with its flagship brand. Through aggressive marketing to a
younger, more upscale and better educated slice of the world's
population, the company is hoping to turn Budweiser into a truly
global brand. By Constance L. Hays.
