<P>
   SCOTUS-ADA (Washington) _ Isolating people with disabilities in
big state institutions when there is no medical reason for their
confinement is a form of discrimination that violates federal
disability law, the Supreme Court ruled Monday.The 6-3 decision, in
a case brought against the state of Georgia by two women with
mental disabilities, was a substantial victory for the disability
rights movement that has looked to the Americans With Disabilities
Act of 1990 as a tool for breaking down institutional walls that
separate people with serious mental and physical problems from the
larger community. By Linda Greenhouse.
