   DELTA-AIRFRANCE _ Delta and Air France say their new exclusive
marketing partnership, announced as expected Tuesday, is the first
step in creating a global alliance to compete with those that
already include several rivals. We also talk to Delta CEO Leo
Mullin, who chalks up a strategic win with the Air France deal
after previously losing a bid to buy Continental and seeing a
domestic alliance with United fizzle. (Thurston, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
