   FBO-BAZEMORE _ Wright Bazemore, who coached Valdosta High
School's football teams during their unprecedented heyday of
national prominence, died Tuesday of an illness. He was 82. He won
268 games, lost 51 and tied 7, a winning percentage of .833, as
head football coach of the Wildcats for 28 years. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
