<P>
   BOERNE, Texas _ While Ripley Arnold and his dragoons were
swatting mosquitoes on the banks of the Trinity and building Fort
Worth, a group of German settlers was chiseling away at the
limestone rocks of the Texas Hill Country, trying to establish
Boerne almost 300 miles to the south. It was 1849 and the Germans
were spreading out over the Hill Country. By ART CHAPMAN. Story has
moved in ``a'' general news category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
