 CHRON   Editors note: The San Francisco Chronicle rounds up the best of 
 the unusual for home and garden in this regular feature, Off the 
 Wall.  
   
   
 OFF THE WALL: Heavens, the Carpet Glows!  
   
   
 By Terry Nagel  
 c. 1999 The San Francisco Chronicle  
   
   
 SAN FRANCISCO _  Reggie Glow leads a double life: subtle and hardly
noticeable during the day, but a real standout when the lights go
down.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Reggie Glow is not anyone you'll ever meet, however. It's a
carpet made by Shaw Industries that glows in the dark.
</P>
<P>
   In natural or incandescent light, it looks like a traditional
carpet. But when the lights are turned off, patterns in the rug pop
out and keep glowing for hours.
</P>
<P>
   Three patterns are available: one with stars, moons and planets
called ``Galactic''; another with sports figures called
``Champions''; and a simple diamond pattern called ``Night
Vision.'' The carpet comes in five colors _ deep blue, burgundy and
three neutral shades _ and costs about $25 per square yard,
installed.
</P>
<P>
   Shaw Industries figures the carpet is ideal for children's rooms
and playrooms.
</P>
<P>
   But you don't need to worry about your kids starting to glow.
George Davies, marketing communications manager of Shaw Industries,
says the carpet isn't radioactive. ``We use an inert mineral that's
environmentally safe. We've actually found a way to extrude it into
the fibers.''
</P>
<P>
   Scotchguard protection is also embedded in the polypropylene
fibers, so you can shampoo the carpet and it won't lose its
luminescence. ``As far as stains goes, this is just about the most
bulletproof fiber you can get,'' says Davies.
</P>
<P>
   And if your child is afraid of the dark, there's an added bonus:
You won't have to buy a night light.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;   &LR;  &QL; 
WHERE TO FIND IT
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR; To find the closest store selling Reggie Glow carpet, call Shaw
Industries of Dalton, Ga., at (800) 441-7429. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
