quiet drought that is afflicting the Northeast from Maine to
Virginia. By Scott Allen. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   FOLKLIFE-FESTIVAL (Washington) _ New Hampshire, South Africa and
Romania _ strange combo as it seems _ will be featured in this
year's Folklife Festival put on by the Smithsonian on the Mall. By
Eun Lee Koh. 750 words
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ENTERTAINMENT (e) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MUSIC-OZAWA (Boston) _ Seiji Ozawa will relinquish his position
as music director of the Boston Symphony Orchestra at the close of
the 2001-02 Tanglewood season to assume the music directorship of
