   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Wednesday, June 23. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
SYMINGTON (Phoenix) - Spot news story on the appellate decision on
former Arizona Gov. Fife Symington, including but not restricted to
the following elements: Details of the appellate panel'ss reasons
for overturning the conviction. Symington's reax and update on what
he has done with himself since leaving office. Can and will the
prosecution try to appeal to the U.S. Supreme Court?Was Judge
Fletcher, the elderly panelist who raised questions about Juror
Cotey's dismissal based on age-related problems, a critical factor
in this decision? If so, how? Is there a dissenting opinion? If so,
what does it say? Legal implication of the case: does this mean
that judicial discretion is being reined in by the appellate court?
Does it conflict with a recent decision in a Tucson case that
strengthened judicial discretion in dismissing jurors from trial
juries? Political reaction: was a governor wrongly unseated? By
CHARLES KELLY, DENNIS WAGNER and JERRY KAMMER. Story will move in
the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
RETRIAL (Phoenix) - Will the prosecution retry the case, and if so,
on which counts? Could they drop some of the counts on which he was
originally convicted, focusing on the strongest one or two? Would
they try to include counts on which he was not convicted,
especially those on which the original jury deadlocked? We should
note that Richard Drooyan, who headed the U.S. Attorney's criminal
division during the Symington investigation, has since left the
office, as has U.S. Attorney Nora Manella. The new U.S. Attorney is
a political appointee with no historical perspective on this case,
nor any face-saving motives to consider. Lead prosecutor David
Schindler will be trying the high-profile Mitnick computer-hacker
case starting in April, and could conceivably leave the office
after that, leaving few of the original players in place. By JERRY
KAMMER. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
FIFE (Phoenix) - What are the chances of Symington renewing his
