thereby making him ineligible? What are his interests now? Can he
reclaim his broker's license? The story should capture Symington's
mood in the wake of the decision, and talk about his prospects and
current and planned activities. By CHRIS MAYES and CHRIS MOESER.
Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
COTEY (Phoenix) - Interview with Mary Jane Cotey, the woman whose
ejection from the Symington jury during deliberations gave rise to
the appeal. By MARY JO PITZL. Story will move in the ``A''
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
BANKRUPTCY (Phoenix) - Update on the Symington bankruptcy case and
how it impinges on his criminal case. By SHAUN MCKINNON and PAT
FLANNERY. Story will move int he ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
PROJECTS (Phoenix) - The status on all of the big projects
developed by Symington while he was filing inconsistent financial
statements. By BILL MULLER, CATHERINE REAGOR and MAX JARMAN. Story
will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
LEGREAX (Phoenix) - Reaction to the appellate court decision on
Symington from friends and foes in the Legislature. By HAL MATTERN
and MIKE MCCLOY. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
BOOKS-NEW (Undated) _ Capsule reviews of new and notable books. By
correspondent ANNE STEPHENSON, Special to the Republic. Story moved
in the ``E'' category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
