NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR WEDNESDAY, JUNE 23
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Wednesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-CIR-WEB-MICROSCOPE-NYT (moved on Wednesday, June 16)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, June
16, about programs that give elementary and high school students
on-line access to scientific technology referred incorrectly to the
Goldstone Apple Valley Radio Telescope Program. The cost is $975
per teacher for training and software; it is not free. And while
universities may provide instructors to help with it in schools,
the program is not available for university students.
