 &UR; WEBOPTIONS _  &LR;  Lots of small businesses are flocking to
toaster-sized ``Internet appliances'' to help them compete on the
Internet with the big boys. These devices, which cost about $1,500
to $3,000 typically let up to 100 employees get and send e-mail,
get information and do research on the Internet, establish and
update Web sites, and protect private files. By Peter Sinton
