e-commerce products for small businesses. Then two weeks ago, it
paid even more to buy Whistle Communications, a Foster City company
that offers easy e-mail and Internet access to small companies.
Both events underscore an important economic fact about the
information technology industry. ``The small-business segment is
growing more quickly than any other,'' said Peter Rowley, general
manager of Global Small Business at IBM. By Peter Sinton
