   &UR; S3 &LR;  _ S3 Inc., the No. 2 designer of fast graphics for PCs,
agreed to buy Diamond Multimedia Systems Inc. for about $173
million in stock, gaining an Internet music player and making what
S3 calls a ``significant strategic shift.'' San Jose-based Diamond
Multimedia makes the Rio MP music player, which plays music
downloaded from the Internet. By Benny Evangelista
</P>
<P>
   &UR; POWER &LR;  _ The ISO, operator of California's high-voltage
transmission system, is pressing federal energy regulators for
permission to rewrite some of the rules governing the state's $23
billion deregulated power market. The request is prompted by market
gouging by Duke Energy Corp., the new owner of some PG&AMP;E power
plants and one of the nation's biggest energy conglomerates. By
Rebecca Smith
