<SLUG> BC-CENTRAL-FLORIDA-CITYWALK-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
UNIVERSAL CREATES RESORT AS THE ULTIMATE `ESCAPE' 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  (Eds: the groove in lowercase is cq) 
 
By SYD KEARNEY 
c.1999 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ORLANDO, Fla. _ As part of its plan to create a destination
resort, Universal is putting together Universal Studios Escape,
encompassing two theme parks, an entertainment complex and three
hotels. And with the opening of Islands of Adventure, most of the
pieces are in place.
</P>
<P>
   Earlier this year, Universal Studios CityWalk began welcoming
guests to its collection of restaurants, nightclubs, specialty
shops and 20-screen movie theater. This summer, Portofino Bay Hotel
will be the first of three Universal resort hotels to open.
</P>
<P>
   CityWalk is a welcome improvement over its California cousin.
While CityWalk Hollywood is a claustrophobia-inducing canyon that
funnels folks from door to door, the Orlando complex is spread over
30 acres. Wide, multilevel boulevards accommodate crowds and allow
space for alfresco dining and street entertainment.
</P>
<P>
   Pick your theme:
</P>
<P>
   _ The cavernous Jimmy Buffett's Margaritaville boasts three
bars, a large indoor stage and a prop plane buzzing above the fray.
The menu is skewed to Key West tastes with specialties such as
conch fritters and calamari. The cheeseburgers are, of course,
paradise.
</P>
<P>
   _ The first NASCAR Cafe is drawing race fans with its rare
artifacts and race simulator. The food is pretty good, too. Try the
revved-up pork chops or the enormous rack of baby-back ribs.
</P>
<P>
   _ The sounds of the Temptations, the Supremes and the Jackson 5
fill the Motown Cafe, which displays music memorabilia and presents
live performances. Check out the Big Chill Lounge after you've
feasted on meatloaf and chicken-fried steak.
</P>
<P>
   _ The world's largest Hard Rock Cafe has a 1959 pink Cadillac
twirling above the bar, which is surrounded by an extensive
music-memorabilia collection. You know the menu: burgers, burgers,
burgers. Rock on.
</P>
<P>
   _ The cuisines of 21 nations have inspired the menu at the Latin
Quarter, which spotlights live salsa, merengue and Latin-rock bands
every night. Among menu staples: plantains, black beans, pork and
yellow rice.
</P>
<P>
   _ The culinary star is Emeril's Restaurant. Instead of live
music, the kitchen staff provides the entertainment: The dining
room is configured around an open kitchen. The Creole-inspired menu
features specialties such as turtle soup, grilled veal chop with
cheesy grits and andouille crusted redfish.
</P>
<P>
   CityWalk nightspots include the reggae-saturated Bob Marley: A
Tribute to Freedom, CityJazz, Pat O'Brien's Orlando and the groove,
a 21st-century nightclub with historically themed lounges.
</P>
<P>
   A highly anticipated addition to CityWalk is NBA City. Scheduled
to open in late summer, the 17,000-square-foot tribute to the
National Basketball Association will feature a restaurant
specializing in contemporary American cuisine, a sports bar, an
interactive playground with an arcade, a retail store and a private
dining room that is expected to be a magnet for visiting NBA stars.
</P>
<P>
   With a weathered-brick and glass exterior and a polished-wood
interior, the building is meant to evoke a sense of basketball
history. Diners will be treated to audio and video programming
produced specifically for NBA City, while sports-bar patrons will
be able to tune in live men's and women's basketball contests or
select from a library of classic games.
</P>
<P>
   While NBA City is causing a buzz, Universal's slam dunk is the
Portofino Bay Hotel.
</P>
<P>
   Designed to resemble an Italian seaside village, the 750-room
luxury hotel is expected to welcome its first guests in early
September. A Lowes Hotel property, the resort will boast five
restaurants, several bars and lounges, a coffeehouse, a
full-service spa, pools and whirlpools, a business center and
retail shops.
</P>
<P>
   One of the hotel features guests will enjoy is curbside
check-in. Guests will be greeted at their car doors by staff
members who will see to their bags and escort them to their rooms,
bypassing the front desk.
</P>
<P>
   Portofino Bay guests also will be provided free transportation
(by water taxi or bus) to the theme parks and CityWalk, early
admission to the parks, priority seating at many restaurants and
shows, and free package delivery from the parks to the hotel. In
addition, resort ID cards will function as charge cards at
restaurants and shops at CityWalk and the theme parks.
</P>
<P>
   Standard room rates for Portofino Bay will start at about $275
per night. Villa Rooms and Suites will offer butler service,
Continental breakfast and evening cocktails and hors d'oeuvres.
</P>
<P>
   For reservations, call 888-322-5541.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
XXX END OF STORY XXX &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
