<HEADLINE>
WHEN YOU GO: UNIVERSAL ESCAPE 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  (Eds: the groove lowercase is cq) 
 
c.1999 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   _ Where: Universal Islands of Adventure, Universal Studios
Florida and Universal Studios CityWalk Orlando are located in
Orlando, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   _ Hours: Islands of Adventure hours vary, but the park generally
is open 9 a.m.-10 p.m. With its movie-related rides and
attractions, Universal Studios Florida is open 9 a.m.-8 p.m. during
the summer. Hours for CityWalk vary, but in general, shops and
restaurants are open 11 a.m.-2 a.m. CityWalk nightclubs open about
5 p.m., while music starts at the hip night spot the groove at 9
nightly.
</P>
<P>
   Fees: Single-day, single-park admission is $44 ($35 for
children). A Universal Studios Escape Pass, good for admission to
both parks within the same day, is available. A two-day Escape pass
is $84.75 ($68.85 for children), a three-day pass is $105.95
($84.75 for children).
</P>
<P>
   There is no admission for CityWalk, but some nightclubs charge a
cover fee. These fees vary from $2 at Pat O'Brien's Orlando to
$5.25 for CityJazz. A CityWalk Party Pass, which allows guests to
bypass cover fees at all venues, is $16.98.
</P>
<P>
   Information: 800-711-0080 or access www.uescape.com.
</P>
